&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Character(char)&lt;br&gt;  A character is represented in ASCII using a numeric code between 0 to 255&lt;br&gt;  Create a character or a string by putting them into a pair of apostrophe(单引号)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;string&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#string&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;string&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;string&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;An array collects characters&lt;br&gt;s1 = ‘Example’&lt;br&gt;s2 = ‘String’&lt;br&gt;String concatenation&lt;br&gt;s3 = [s1 s2]&lt;br&gt;s4 = [s1;s2]    -&amp;gt; 两个字符串长度必须相等&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Logical Operations and Assignments&lt;br&gt;  Many numerical and logical operators can be applied to strings&lt;br&gt;  e.g.    str = ‘aardvark’    ‘a’ = str 返回1和0的向量&lt;br&gt;  (和每一个都进行比较)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
